6264 
6265  /// @}
6266 
6267  //////////////////////////////////////////
6268  // binary serialization/deserialization //
6269  //////////////////////////////////////////
6270 
6271  /// @name binary serialization/deserialization support
6272  /// @{
6273 
6274  private:
6275  template<typename T>
6276  static void add_to_vector(std::vector<uint8_t>& vec, size_t bytes, const T number)
6277  {
6278  assert(bytes == 1 or bytes == 2 or bytes == 4 or bytes == 8);
6279 
6280  switch (bytes)
6281  {
6282  case 8:
6283  {
6284  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 070) & 0xff));
6285  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 060) & 0xff));
6286  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 050) & 0xff));
6287  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 040) & 0xff));
6288  // intentional fall-through
6289  }
6290 
6291  case 4:
6292  {
6293  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 030) & 0xff));
6294  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 020) & 0xff));
6295  // intentional fall-through
6296  }
6297 
6298  case 2:
6299  {
6300  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 010) & 0xff));
6301  // intentional fall-through
6302  }
6303 
6304  case 1:
6305  {
6306  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(number & 0xff));
6307  break;
6308  }
6309  }
6310  }
6311 
6312  /*!
6313  @brief take sufficient bytes from a vector to fill an integer variable
6314 
6315  In the context of binary serialization formats, we need to read several
6316  bytes from a byte vector and combine them to multi-byte integral data
6317  types.
6318 
6319  @param[in] vec byte vector to read from
6320  @param[in] current_index the position in the vector after which to read
6321 
6322  @return the next sizeof(T) bytes from @a vec, in reverse order as T
6323 
6324  @tparam T the integral return type
6325 
6326  @throw std::out_of_range if there are less than sizeof(T)+1 bytes in the
6327  vector @a vec to read
6328 
6329  In the for loop, the bytes from the vector are copied in reverse order into
6330  the return value. In the figures below, let sizeof(T)=4 and `i` be the loop
6331  variable.
6332 
6333  Precondition:
6334 
6335  vec: | | | a | b | c | d | T: | | | | |
6336  ^ ^ ^ ^
6337  current_index i ptr sizeof(T)
6338 
6339  Postcondition:
6340 
6341  vec: | | | a | b | c | d | T: | d | c | b | a |
6342  ^ ^ ^
6343  | i ptr
6344  current_index
6345 
6346  @sa Code adapted from <http://stackoverflow.com/a/41031865/266378>.
6347  */
6348  template<typename T>
6349  static T get_from_vector(const std::vector<uint8_t>& vec, const size_t current_index)
6350  {
6351  if (current_index + sizeof(T) + 1 > vec.size())
6352  {
6353  throw std::out_of_range("cannot read " + std::to_string(sizeof(T)) + " bytes from vector");
6354  }
6355 
6356  T result;
6357  auto* ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&result);
6358  for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(T); ++i)
6359  {
6360  *ptr++ = vec[current_index + sizeof(T) - i];
6361  }
6362  return result;
6363  }
6364 
6365  /*!
6366  @brief create a MessagePack serialization of a given JSON value
6367 
6368  This is a straightforward implementation of the MessagePack specification.
6369 
6370  @param[in] j JSON value to serialize
6371  @param[in,out] v byte vector to write the serialization to
6372 
6373  @sa https://github.com/msgpack/msgpack/blob/master/spec.md
6374  */
6375  static void to_msgpack_internal(const basic_json& j, std::vector<uint8_t>& v)
6376  {
6377  switch (j.type())
6378  {
6379  case value_t::null:
6380  {
6381  // nil
6382  v.push_back(0xc0);
6383  break;
6384  }
6385 
6386  case value_t::boolean:
6387  {
6388  // true and false
6389  v.push_back(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xc3 : 0xc2);
6390  break;
6391  }
6392 
6393  case value_t::number_integer:
6394  {
6395  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
6396  {
6397  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
6398  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we
6399  // used the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case
6400  // here.
6401  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
6402  {
6403  // positive fixnum
6404  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6405  }
6406  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT8_MAX)
6407  {
6408  // uint 8
6409  v.push_back(0xcc);
6410  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6411  }
6412  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT16_MAX)
6413  {
6414  // uint 16
6415  v.push_back(0xcd);
6416  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6417  }
6418  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT32_MAX)
6419  {
6420  // uint 32
6421  v.push_back(0xce);
6422  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6423  }
6424  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT64_MAX)
6425  {
6426  // uint 64
6427  v.push_back(0xcf);
6428  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6429  }
6430  }
6431  else
6432  {
6433  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
6434  {
6435  // negative fixnum
6436  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6437  }
6438  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= INT8_MIN and j.m_value.number_integer <= INT8_MAX)
6439  {
6440  // int 8
6441  v.push_back(0xd0);
6442  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6443  }
6444  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= INT16_MIN and j.m_value.number_integer <= INT16_MAX)
6445  {
6446  // int 16
6447  v.push_back(0xd1);
6448  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_integer);
6449  }
6450  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= INT32_MIN and j.m_value.number_integer <= INT32_MAX)
6451  {
6452  // int 32
6453  v.push_back(0xd2);
6454  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_integer);
6455  }
6456  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= INT64_MIN and j.m_value.number_integer <= INT64_MAX)
6457  {
6458  // int 64
6459  v.push_back(0xd3);
6460  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_integer);
6461  }
6462  }
6463  break;
6464  }
6465 
6466  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6467  {
6468  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
6469  {
6470  // positive fixnum
6471  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6472  }
6473  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT8_MAX)
6474  {
6475  // uint 8
6476  v.push_back(0xcc);
6477  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6478  }
6479  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT16_MAX)
6480  {
6481  // uint 16
6482  v.push_back(0xcd);
6483  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6484  }
6485  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT32_MAX)
6486  {
6487  // uint 32
6488  v.push_back(0xce);
6489  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6490  }
6491  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= UINT64_MAX)
6492  {
6493  // uint 64
6494  v.push_back(0xcf);
6495  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6496  }
6497  break;
6498  }
6499 
6500  case value_t::number_float:
6501  {
6502  // float 64
6503  v.push_back(0xcb);
6504  const auto* helper = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&(j.m_value.number_float));
6505  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i)
6506  {
6507  v.push_back(helper[7 - i]);
6508  }
6509  break;
6510  }
6511 
6512  case value_t::string:
6513  {
6514  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6515  if (N <= 31)
6516  {
6517  // fixstr
6518  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xa0 | N));
6519  }
6520  else if (N <= 255)
6521  {
6522  // str 8
6523  v.push_back(0xd9);
6524  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6525  }
6526  else if (N <= 65535)
6527  {
6528  // str 16
6529  v.push_back(0xda);
6530  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6531  }
6532  else if (N <= 4294967295)
6533  {
6534  // str 32
6535  v.push_back(0xdb);
6536  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6537  }
6538 
6539  // append string
6540  std::copy(j.m_value.string->begin(), j.m_value.string->end(),
6541  std::back_inserter(v));
6542  break;
6543  }
6544 
6545  case value_t::array:
6546  {
6547  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6548  if (N <= 15)
6549  {
6550  // fixarray
6551  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
6552  }
6553  else if (N <= 0xffff)
6554  {
6555  // array 16
6556  v.push_back(0xdc);
6557  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6558  }
6559  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
6560  {
6561  // array 32
6562  v.push_back(0xdd);
6563  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6564  }
6565 
6566  // append each element
6567  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
6568  {
6569  to_msgpack_internal(el, v);
6570  }
6571  break;
6572  }
6573 
6574  case value_t::object:
6575  {
6576  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6577  if (N <= 15)
6578  {
6579  // fixmap
6580  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xf)));
6581  }
6582  else if (N <= 65535)
6583  {
6584  // map 16
6585  v.push_back(0xde);
6586  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6587  }
6588  else if (N <= 4294967295)
6589  {
6590  // map 32
6591  v.push_back(0xdf);
6592  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6593  }
6594 
6595  // append each element
6596  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
6597  {
6598  to_msgpack_internal(el.first, v);
6599  to_msgpack_internal(el.second, v);
6600  }
6601  break;
6602  }
6603 
6604  default:
6605  {
6606  break;
6607  }
6608  }
6609  }
6610 
6611  /*!
6612  @brief create a CBOR serialization of a given JSON value
6613 
6614  This is a straightforward implementation of the CBOR specification.
6615 
6616  @param[in] j JSON value to serialize
6617  @param[in,out] v byte vector to write the serialization to
6618 
6619  @sa https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7049
6620  */
6621  static void to_cbor_internal(const basic_json& j, std::vector<uint8_t>& v)
6622  {
6623  switch (j.type())
6624  {
6625  case value_t::null:
6626  {
6627  v.push_back(0xf6);
6628  break;
6629  }
6630 
6631  case value_t::boolean:
6632  {
6633  v.push_back(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xf5 : 0xf4);
6634  break;
6635  }
6636 
6637  case value_t::number_integer:
6638  {
6639  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
6640  {
6641  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
6642  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
6643  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
6644  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
6645  {
6646  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6647  }
6648  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= UINT8_MAX)
6649  {
6650  v.push_back(0x18);
6651  // one-byte uint8_t
6652  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6653  }
6654  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= UINT16_MAX)
6655  {
6656  v.push_back(0x19);
6657  // two-byte uint16_t
6658  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_integer);
6659  }
6660  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= UINT32_MAX)
6661  {
6662  v.push_back(0x1a);
6663  // four-byte uint32_t
6664  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_integer);
6665  }
6666  else
6667  {
6668  v.push_back(0x1b);
6669  // eight-byte uint64_t
6670  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_integer);
6671  }
6672  }
6673  else
6674  {
6675  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
6676  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
6677  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
6678  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
6679  {
6680  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
6681  }
6682  else if (positive_number <= UINT8_MAX)
6683  {
6684  // int 8
6685  v.push_back(0x38);
6686  add_to_vector(v, 1, positive_number);
6687  }
6688  else if (positive_number <= UINT16_MAX)
6689  {
6690  // int 16
6691  v.push_back(0x39);
6692  add_to_vector(v, 2, positive_number);
6693  }
6694  else if (positive_number <= UINT32_MAX)
6695  {
6696  // int 32
6697  v.push_back(0x3a);
6698  add_to_vector(v, 4, positive_number);
6699  }
6700  else
6701  {
6702  // int 64
6703  v.push_back(0x3b);
6704  add_to_vector(v, 8, positive_number);
6705  }
6706  }
6707  break;
6708  }
6709 
6710  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6711  {
6712  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
6713  {
6714  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6715  }
6716  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xff)
6717  {
6718  v.push_back(0x18);
6719  // one-byte uint8_t
6720  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6721  }
6722  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffff)
6723  {
6724  v.push_back(0x19);
6725  // two-byte uint16_t
6726  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6727  }
6728  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffffffff)
6729  {
6730  v.push_back(0x1a);
6731  // four-byte uint32_t
6732  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6733  }
6734  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
6735  {
6736  v.push_back(0x1b);
6737  // eight-byte uint64_t
6738  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6739  }
6740  break;
6741  }
6742 
6743  case value_t::number_float:
6744  {
6745  // Double-Precision Float
6746  v.push_back(0xfb);
6747  const auto* helper = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&(j.m_value.number_float));
6748  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i)
6749  {
6750  v.push_back(helper[7 - i]);
6751  }
6752  break;
6753  }
6754 
6755  case value_t::string:
6756  {
6757  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6758  if (N <= 0x17)
6759  {
6760  v.push_back(0x60 + N); // 1 byte for string + size
6761  }
6762  else if (N <= 0xff)
6763  {
6764  v.push_back(0x78); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6765  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6766  }
6767  else if (N <= 0xffff)
6768  {
6769  v.push_back(0x79); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6770  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6771  }
6772  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
6773  {
6774  v.push_back(0x7a); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6775  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6776  }
6777  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6778  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
6779  {
6780  v.push_back(0x7b); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6781  add_to_vector(v, 8, N);
6782  }
6783  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6784 
6785  // append string
6786  std::copy(j.m_value.string->begin(), j.m_value.string->end(),
6787  std::back_inserter(v));
6788  break;
6789  }
6790 
6791  case value_t::array:
6792  {
6793  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6794  if (N <= 0x17)
6795  {
6796  v.push_back(0x80 + N); // 1 byte for array + size
6797  }
6798  else if (N <= 0xff)
6799  {
6800  v.push_back(0x98); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6801  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6802  }
6803  else if (N <= 0xffff)
6804  {
6805  v.push_back(0x99); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6806  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6807  }
6808  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
6809  {
6810  v.push_back(0x9a); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6811  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6812  }
6813  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6814  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
6815  {
6816  v.push_back(0x9b); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6817  add_to_vector(v, 8, N);
6818  }
6819  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6820 
6821  // append each element
6822  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
6823  {
6824  to_cbor_internal(el, v);
6825  }
6826  break;
6827  }
6828 
6829  case value_t::object:
6830  {
6831  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6832  if (N <= 0x17)
6833  {
6834  v.push_back(0xa0 + N); // 1 byte for object + size
6835  }
6836  else if (N <= 0xff)
6837  {
6838  v.push_back(0xb8);
6839  add_to_vector(v, 1, N); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6840  }
6841  else if (N <= 0xffff)
6842  {
6843  v.push_back(0xb9);
6844  add_to_vector(v, 2, N); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6845  }
6846  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
6847  {
6848  v.push_back(0xba);
6849  add_to_vector(v, 4, N); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6850  }
6851  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6852  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
6853  {
6854  v.push_back(0xbb);
6855  add_to_vector(v, 8, N); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6856  }
6857  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6858 
6859  // append each element
6860  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
6861  {
6862  to_cbor_internal(el.first, v);
6863  to_cbor_internal(el.second, v);
6864  }
6865  break;
6866  }
6867 
6868  default:
6869  {
6870  break;
6871  }
6872  }
6873  }
6874 
6875 
6876  /*
6877  @brief checks if given lengths do not exceed the size of a given vector
6878 
6879  To secure the access to the byte vector during CBOR/MessagePack
6880  deserialization, bytes are copied from the vector into buffers. This
6881  function checks if the number of bytes to copy (@a len) does not exceed
6882  the size @s size of the vector. Additionally, an @a offset is given from
6883  where to start reading the bytes.
6884 
6885  This function checks whether reading the bytes is safe; that is, offset is
6886  a valid index in the vector, offset+len
6887 
6888  @param[in] size size of the byte vector
6889  @param[in] len number of bytes to read
6890  @param[in] offset offset where to start reading
6891 
6892  vec: x x x x x X X X X X
6893  ^ ^ ^
6894  0 offset len
6895 
6896  @throws out_of_range if `len > v.size()`
6897  */
6898  static void check_length(const size_t size, const size_t len, const size_t offset)
6899  {
6900  // simple case: requested length is greater than the vector's length
6901  if (len > size or offset > size)
6902  {
6903  throw std::out_of_range("len out of range");
6904  }
6905 
6906  // second case: adding offset would result in overflow
6907  if ((size > (std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max() - offset)))
6908  {
6909  throw std::out_of_range("len+offset out of range");
6910  }
6911 
6912  // last case: reading past the end of the vector
6913  if (len + offset > size)
6914  {
6915  throw std::out_of_range("len+offset out of range");
6916  }
6917  }
6918 
6919  /*!
6920  @brief create a JSON value from a given MessagePack vector
6921 
6922  @param[in] v MessagePack serialization
6923  @param[in] idx byte index to start reading from @a v
6924 
6925  @return deserialized JSON value
6926 
6927  @throw std::invalid_argument if unsupported features from MessagePack were
6928  used in the given vector @a v or if the input is not valid MessagePack
6929  @throw std::out_of_range if the given vector ends prematurely
6930 
6931  @sa https://github.com/msgpack/msgpack/blob/master/spec.md
6932  */
6933  static basic_json from_msgpack_internal(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v, size_t& idx)
6934  {
6935  // make sure reading 1 byte is safe
6936  check_length(v.size(), 1, idx);
6937 
6938  // store and increment index
6939  const size_t current_idx = idx++;
6940 
6941  if (v[current_idx] <= 0xbf)
6942  {
6943  if (v[current_idx] <= 0x7f) // positive fixint
6944  {
6945  return v[current_idx];
6946  }
6947  if (v[current_idx] <= 0x8f) // fixmap
6948  {
6949  basic_json result = value_t::object;
6950  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x0f;
6951  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6952  {
6953  std::string key = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
6954  result[key] = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
6955  }
6956  return result;
6957  }
6958  else if (v[current_idx] <= 0x9f) // fixarray
6959  {
6960  basic_json result = value_t::array;
6961  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x0f;
6962  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
6963  {
6964  result.push_back(from_msgpack_internal(v, idx));
6965  }
6966  return result;
6967  }
6968  else // fixstr
6969  {
6970  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x1f;
6971  const size_t offset = current_idx + 1;
6972  idx += len; // skip content bytes
6973  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
6974  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
6975  }
6976  }
6977  else if (v[current_idx] >= 0xe0) // negative fixint
6978  {
6979  return static_cast<int8_t>(v[current_idx]);
6980  }
6981  else
6982  {
6983  switch (v[current_idx])
6984  {
6985  case 0xc0: // nil
6986  {
6987  return value_t::null;
6988  }
6989 
6990  case 0xc2: // false
6991  {
6992  return false;
6993  }
6994 
6995  case 0xc3: // true
6996  {
6997  return true;
6998  }
6999 
7000  case 0xca: // float 32
7001  {
7002  // copy bytes in reverse order into the double variable
7003  float res;
7004  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(float); ++byte)
7005  {
7006  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(float) - byte - 1] = v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7007  }
7008  idx += sizeof(float); // skip content bytes
7009  return res;
7010  }
7011 
7012  case 0xcb: // float 64
7013  {
7014  // copy bytes in reverse order into the double variable
7015  double res;
7016  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(double); ++byte)
7017  {
7018  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(double) - byte - 1] = v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7019  }
7020  idx += sizeof(double); // skip content bytes
7021  return res;
7022  }
7023 
7024  case 0xcc: // uint 8
7025  {
7026  idx += 1; // skip content byte
7027  return get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx);
7028  }
7029 
7030  case 0xcd: // uint 16
7031  {
7032  idx += 2; // skip 2 content bytes
7033  return get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx);
7034  }
7035 
7036  case 0xce: // uint 32
7037  {
7038  idx += 4; // skip 4 content bytes
7039  return get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx);
7040  }
7041 
7042  case 0xcf: // uint 64
7043  {
7044  idx += 8; // skip 8 content bytes
7045  return get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx);
7046  }
7047 
7048  case 0xd0: // int 8
7049  {
7050  idx += 1; // skip content byte
7051  return get_from_vector<int8_t>(v, current_idx);
7052  }
7053 
7054  case 0xd1: // int 16
7055  {
7056  idx += 2; // skip 2 content bytes
7057  return get_from_vector<int16_t>(v, current_idx);
7058  }
7059 
7060  case 0xd2: // int 32
7061  {
7062  idx += 4; // skip 4 content bytes
7063  return get_from_vector<int32_t>(v, current_idx);
7064  }
7065 
7066  case 0xd3: // int 64
7067  {
7068  idx += 8; // skip 8 content bytes
7069  return get_from_vector<int64_t>(v, current_idx);
7070  }
7071 
7072  case 0xd9: // str 8
7073  {
7074  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx));
7075  const size_t offset = current_idx + 2;
7076  idx += len + 1; // skip size byte + content bytes
7077  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7078  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7079  }
7080 
7081  case 0xda: // str 16
7082  {
7083  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7084  const size_t offset = current_idx + 3;
7085  idx += len + 2; // skip 2 size bytes + content bytes
7086  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7087  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7088  }
7089 
7090  case 0xdb: // str 32
7091  {
7092  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7093  const size_t offset = current_idx + 5;
7094  idx += len + 4; // skip 4 size bytes + content bytes
7095  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7096  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7097  }
7098 
7099  case 0xdc: // array 16
7100  {
7101  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7102  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7103  idx += 2; // skip 2 size bytes
7104  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7105  {
7106  result.push_back(from_msgpack_internal(v, idx));
7107  }
7108  return result;
7109  }
7110 
7111  case 0xdd: // array 32
7112  {
7113  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7114  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7115  idx += 4; // skip 4 size bytes
7116  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7117  {
7118  result.push_back(from_msgpack_internal(v, idx));
7119  }
7120  return result;
7121  }
7122 
7123  case 0xde: // map 16
7124  {
7125  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7126  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7127  idx += 2; // skip 2 size bytes
7128  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7129  {
7130  std::string key = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
7131  result[key] = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
7132  }
7133  return result;
7134  }
7135 
7136  case 0xdf: // map 32
7137  {
7138  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7139  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7140  idx += 4; // skip 4 size bytes
7141  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7142  {
7143  std::string key = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
7144  result[key] = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
7145  }
7146  return result;
7147  }
7148 
7149  default:
7150  {
7151  throw std::invalid_argument("error parsing a msgpack @ " + std::to_string(current_idx) + ": " + std::to_string(static_cast<int>(v[current_idx])));
7152  }
7153  }
7154  }
7155  }
7156 
7157  /*!
7158  @brief create a JSON value from a given CBOR vector
7159 
7160  @param[in] v CBOR serialization
7161  @param[in] idx byte index to start reading from @a v
7162 
7163  @return deserialized JSON value
7164 
7165  @throw std::invalid_argument if unsupported features from CBOR were used in
7166  the given vector @a v or if the input is not valid CBOR
7167  @throw std::out_of_range if the given vector ends prematurely
7168 
7169  @sa https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7049
7170  */
7171  static basic_json from_cbor_internal(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v, size_t& idx)
7172  {
7173  // store and increment index
7174  const size_t current_idx = idx++;
7175 
7176  switch (v.at(current_idx))
7177  {
7178  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
7179  case 0x00:
7180  case 0x01:
7181  case 0x02:
7182  case 0x03:
7183  case 0x04:
7184  case 0x05:
7185  case 0x06:
7186  case 0x07:
7187  case 0x08:
7188  case 0x09:
7189  case 0x0a:
7190  case 0x0b:
7191  case 0x0c:
7192  case 0x0d:
7193  case 0x0e:
7194  case 0x0f:
7195  case 0x10:
7196  case 0x11:
7197  case 0x12:
7198  case 0x13:
7199  case 0x14:
7200  case 0x15:
7201  case 0x16:
7202  case 0x17:
7203  {
7204  return v[current_idx];
7205  }
7206 
7207  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
7208  {
7209  idx += 1; // skip content byte
7210  return get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx);
7211  }
7212 
7213  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
7214  {
7215  idx += 2; // skip 2 content bytes
7216  return get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx);
7217  }
7218 
7219  case 0x1a: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
7220  {
7221  idx += 4; // skip 4 content bytes
7222  return get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx);
7223  }
7224 
7225  case 0x1b: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
7226  {
7227  idx += 8; // skip 8 content bytes
7228  return get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx);
7229  }
7230 
7231  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
7232  case 0x20:
7233  case 0x21:
7234  case 0x22:
7235  case 0x23:
7236  case 0x24:
7237  case 0x25:
7238  case 0x26:
7239  case 0x27:
7240  case 0x28:
7241  case 0x29:
7242  case 0x2a:
7243  case 0x2b:
7244  case 0x2c:
7245  case 0x2d:
7246  case 0x2e:
7247  case 0x2f:
7248  case 0x30:
7249  case 0x31:
7250  case 0x32:
7251  case 0x33:
7252  case 0x34:
7253  case 0x35:
7254  case 0x36:
7255  case 0x37:
7256  {
7257  return static_cast<int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - v[current_idx]);
7258  }
7259 
7260  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
7261  {
7262  idx += 1; // skip content byte
7263  // must be uint8_t !
7264  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx);
7265  }
7266 
7267  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
7268  {
7269  idx += 2; // skip 2 content bytes
7270  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx);
7271  }
7272 
7273  case 0x3a: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
7274  {
7275  idx += 4; // skip 4 content bytes
7276  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx);
7277  }
7278 
7279  case 0x3b: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
7280  {
7281  idx += 8; // skip 8 content bytes
7282  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - static_cast<number_integer_t>(get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx));
7283  }
7284 
7285  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
7286  case 0x60:
7287  case 0x61:
7288  case 0x62:
7289  case 0x63:
7290  case 0x64:
7291  case 0x65:
7292  case 0x66:
7293  case 0x67:
7294  case 0x68:
7295  case 0x69:
7296  case 0x6a:
7297  case 0x6b:
7298  case 0x6c:
7299  case 0x6d:
7300  case 0x6e:
7301  case 0x6f:
7302  case 0x70:
7303  case 0x71:
7304  case 0x72:
7305  case 0x73:
7306  case 0x74:
7307  case 0x75:
7308  case 0x76:
7309  case 0x77:
7310  {
7311  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(v[current_idx] - 0x60);
7312  const size_t offset = current_idx + 1;
7313  idx += len; // skip content bytes
7314  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7315  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7316  }
7317 
7318  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
7319  {
7320  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx));
7321  const size_t offset = current_idx + 2;
7322  idx += len + 1; // skip size byte + content bytes
7323  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7324  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7325  }
7326 
7327  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
7328  {
7329  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7330  const size_t offset = current_idx + 3;
7331  idx += len + 2; // skip 2 size bytes + content bytes
7332  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7333  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7334  }
7335 
7336  case 0x7a: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
7337  {
7338  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7339  const size_t offset = current_idx + 5;
7340  idx += len + 4; // skip 4 size bytes + content bytes
7341  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7342  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7343  }
7344 
7345  case 0x7b: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
7346  {
7347  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx));
7348  const size_t offset = current_idx + 9;
7349  idx += len + 8; // skip 8 size bytes + content bytes
7350  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
7351  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset, len);
7352  }
7353 
7354  case 0x7f: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
7355  {
7356  std::string result;
7357  while (v.at(idx) != 0xff)
7358  {
7359  string_t s = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7360  result += s;
7361  }
7362  // skip break byte (0xFF)
7363  idx += 1;
7364  return result;
7365  }
7366 
7367  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
7368  case 0x80:
7369  case 0x81:
7370  case 0x82:
7371  case 0x83:
7372  case 0x84:
7373  case 0x85:
7374  case 0x86:
7375  case 0x87:
7376  case 0x88:
7377  case 0x89:
7378  case 0x8a:
7379  case 0x8b:
7380  case 0x8c:
7381  case 0x8d:
7382  case 0x8e:
7383  case 0x8f:
7384  case 0x90:
7385  case 0x91:
7386  case 0x92:
7387  case 0x93:
7388  case 0x94:
7389  case 0x95:
7390  case 0x96:
7391  case 0x97:
7392  {
7393  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7394  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(v[current_idx] - 0x80);
7395  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7396  {
7397  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7398  }
7399  return result;
7400  }
7401 
7402  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
7403  {
7404  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7405  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx));
7406  idx += 1; // skip 1 size byte
7407  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7408  {
7409  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7410  }
7411  return result;
7412  }
7413 
7414  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
7415  {
7416  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7417  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7418  idx += 2; // skip 4 size bytes
7419  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7420  {
7421  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7422  }
7423  return result;
7424  }
7425 
7426  case 0x9a: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
7427  {
7428  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7429  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7430  idx += 4; // skip 4 size bytes
7431  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7432  {
7433  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7434  }
7435  return result;
7436  }
7437 
7438  case 0x9b: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
7439  {
7440  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7441  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx));
7442  idx += 8; // skip 8 size bytes
7443  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7444  {
7445  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7446  }
7447  return result;
7448  }
7449 
7450  case 0x9f: // array (indefinite length)
7451  {
7452  basic_json result = value_t::array;
7453  while (v.at(idx) != 0xff)
7454  {
7455  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7456  }
7457  // skip break byte (0xFF)
7458  idx += 1;
7459  return result;
7460  }
7461 
7462  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
7463  case 0xa0:
7464  case 0xa1:
7465  case 0xa2:
7466  case 0xa3:
7467  case 0xa4:
7468  case 0xa5:
7469  case 0xa6:
7470  case 0xa7:
7471  case 0xa8:
7472  case 0xa9:
7473  case 0xaa:
7474  case 0xab:
7475  case 0xac:
7476  case 0xad:
7477  case 0xae:
7478  case 0xaf:
7479  case 0xb0:
7480  case 0xb1:
7481  case 0xb2:
7482  case 0xb3:
7483  case 0xb4:
7484  case 0xb5:
7485  case 0xb6:
7486  case 0xb7:
7487  {
7488  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7489  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(v[current_idx] - 0xa0);
7490  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7491  {
7492  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7493  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7494  }
7495  return result;
7496  }
7497 
7498  case 0xb8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
7499  {
7500  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7501  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx));
7502  idx += 1; // skip 1 size byte
7503  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7504  {
7505  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7506  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7507  }
7508  return result;
7509  }
7510 
7511  case 0xb9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
7512  {
7513  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7514  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7515  idx += 2; // skip 2 size bytes
7516  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7517  {
7518  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7519  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7520  }
7521  return result;
7522  }
7523 
7524  case 0xba: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
7525  {
7526  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7527  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7528  idx += 4; // skip 4 size bytes
7529  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7530  {
7531  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7532  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7533  }
7534  return result;
7535  }
7536 
7537  case 0xbb: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
7538  {
7539  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7540  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx));
7541  idx += 8; // skip 8 size bytes
7542  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
7543  {
7544  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7545  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7546  }
7547  return result;
7548  }
7549 
7550  case 0xbf: // map (indefinite length)
7551  {
7552  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7553  while (v.at(idx) != 0xff)
7554  {
7555  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7556  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7557  }
7558  // skip break byte (0xFF)
7559  idx += 1;
7560  return result;
7561  }
7562 
7563  case 0xf4: // false
7564  {
7565  return false;
7566  }
7567 
7568  case 0xf5: // true
7569  {
7570  return true;
7571  }
7572 
7573  case 0xf6: // null
7574  {
7575  return value_t::null;
7576  }
7577 
7578  case 0xf9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
7579  {
7580  idx += 2; // skip two content bytes
7581 
7582  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
7583  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added to
7584  // IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often still
7585  // only have limited support for them. It is very easy to
7586  // include at least decoding support for them even without such
7587  // support. An example of a small decoder for half-precision
7588  // floating-point numbers in the C language is shown in Fig. 3.
7589  const int half = (v.at(current_idx + 1) << 8) + v.at(current_idx + 2);
7590  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1f;
7591  const int mant = half & 0x3ff;
7592  double val;
7593  if (exp == 0)
7594  {
7595  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
7596  }
7597  else if (exp != 31)
7598  {
7599  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
7600  }
7601  else
7602  {
7603  val = mant == 0 ? INFINITY : NAN;
7604  }
7605  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
7606  }
7607 
7608  case 0xfa: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
7609  {
7610  // copy bytes in reverse order into the float variable
7611  float res;
7612  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(float); ++byte)
7613  {
7614  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(float) - byte - 1] = v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7615  }
7616  idx += sizeof(float); // skip content bytes
7617  return res;
7618  }
7619 
7620  case 0xfb: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
7621  {
7622  // copy bytes in reverse order into the double variable
7623  double res;
7624  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(double); ++byte)
7625  {
7626  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(double) - byte - 1] = v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7627  }
7628  idx += sizeof(double); // skip content bytes
7629  return res;
7630  }
7631 
7632  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
7633  {
7634  throw std::invalid_argument("error parsing a CBOR @ " + std::to_string(current_idx) + ": " + std::to_string(static_cast<int>(v[current_idx])));
7635  }
7636  }
7637  }
7638 
7639  public:
7640  /*!
7641  @brief create a MessagePack serialization of a given JSON value
7642 
7643  Serializes a given JSON value @a j to a byte vector using the MessagePack
7644  serialization format. MessagePack is a binary serialization format which
7645  aims to be more compact than JSON itself, yet more efficient to parse.
7646 
7647  @param[in] j JSON value to serialize
7648  @return MessagePack serialization as byte vector
7649 
7650  @complexity Linear in the size of the JSON value @a j.
7651 
7652  @liveexample{The example shows the serialization of a JSON value to a byte
7653  vector in MessagePack format.,to_msgpack}
7654 
7655  @sa http://msgpack.org
7656  @sa @ref from_msgpack(const std::vector<uint8_t>&) for the analogous
7657  deserialization
7658  @sa @ref to_cbor(const basic_json& for the related CBOR format
7659  */
7660  static std::vector<uint8_t> to_msgpack(const basic_json& j)
7661  {
7662  std::vector<uint8_t> result;
7663  to_msgpack_internal(j, result);
7664  return result;
7665  }
7666 
7667  /*!
7668  @brief create a JSON value from a byte vector in MessagePack format
7669 
7670  Deserializes a given byte vector @a v to a JSON value using the MessagePack
7671  serialization format.
7672 
7673  @param[in] v a byte vector in MessagePack format
7674  @return deserialized JSON value
7675 
7676  @throw std::invalid_argument if unsupported features from MessagePack were
7677  used in the given vector @a v or if the input is not valid MessagePack
7678  @throw std::out_of_range if the given vector ends prematurely
7679 
7680  @complexity Linear in the size of the byte vector @a v.
7681 
7682  @liveexample{The example shows the deserialization of a byte vector in
7683  MessagePack format to a JSON value.,from_msgpack}
7684 
7685  @sa http://msgpack.org
7686  @sa @ref to_msgpack(const basic_json&) for the analogous serialization
7687  @sa @ref from_cbor(const std::vector<uint8_t>&) for the related CBOR format
7688  */
7689  static basic_json from_msgpack(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v)
7690  {
7691  size_t i = 0;
7692  return from_msgpack_internal(v, i);
7693  }
7694 
7695  /*!
7696  @brief create a MessagePack serialization of a given JSON value
7697 
7698  Serializes a given JSON value @a j to a byte vector using the CBOR (Concise
7699  Binary Object Representation) serialization format. CBOR is a binary
7700  serialization format which aims to be more compact than JSON itself, yet
7701  more efficient to parse.
7702 
7703  @param[in] j JSON value to serialize
7704  @return MessagePack serialization as byte vector
7705 
7706  @complexity Linear in the size of the JSON value @a j.
7707 
7708  @liveexample{The example shows the serialization of a JSON value to a byte
7709  vector in CBOR format.,to_cbor}
7710 
7711  @sa http://cbor.io
7712  @sa @ref from_cbor(const std::vector<uint8_t>&) for the analogous
7713  deserialization
7714  @sa @ref to_msgpack(const basic_json& for the related MessagePack format
7715  */
7716  static std::vector<uint8_t> to_cbor(const basic_json& j)
7717  {
7718  std::vector<uint8_t> result;
7719  to_cbor_internal(j, result);
7720  return result;
7721  }
7722 
7723  /*!
7724  @brief create a JSON value from a byte vector in CBOR format
7725 
7726  Deserializes a given byte vector @a v to a JSON value using the CBOR
7727  (Concise Binary Object Representation) serialization format.
7728 
7729  @param[in] v a byte vector in CBOR format
7730  @return deserialized JSON value
7731 
7732  @throw std::invalid_argument if unsupported features from CBOR were used in
7733  the given vector @a v or if the input is not valid MessagePack
7734  @throw std::out_of_range if the given vector ends prematurely
7735 
7736  @complexity Linear in the size of the byte vector @a v.
7737 
7738  @liveexample{The example shows the deserialization of a byte vector in CBOR
7739  format to a JSON value.,from_cbor}
7740 
7741  @sa http://cbor.io
7742  @sa @ref to_cbor(const basic_json&) for the analogous serialization
7743  @sa @ref from_msgpack(const std::vector<uint8_t>&) for the related
7744  MessagePack format
7745  */
7746  static basic_json from_cbor(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v)
7747  {
7748  size_t i = 0;
7749  return from_cbor_internal(v, i);
7750  }
7751 
7752  /// @}
7753 
7754  private:
7755  ///////////////////////////
7756  // convenience functions //
7757  ///////////////////////////
7758 
7759  /*!
7760  @brief return the type as string
7761 
7762  Returns the type name as string to be used in error messages - usually to
7763  indicate that a function was called on a wrong JSON type.
7764 
7765  @return basically a string representation of a the @a m_type member
7766 
7767  @complexity Constant.
7768 
7769  @since version 1.0.0
7770  */
7771  std::string type_name() const
7772  {
7773  switch (m_type)
7774  {
7775  case value_t::null:
7776  return "null";
7777  case value_t::object:
7778  return "object";
7779  case value_t::array:
7780  return "array";
7781  case value_t::string:
7782  return "string";
7783  case value_t::boolean:
7784  return "boolean";
7785  case value_t::discarded:
7786  return "discarded";
7787  default:
7788  return "number";
7789  }
7790  }
7791 
7792  /*!
7793  @brief calculates the extra space to escape a JSON string
7794 
7795  @param[in] s the string to escape
7796  @return the number of characters required to escape string @a s
7797 
7798  @complexity Linear in the length of string @a s.
7799  */
7800  static std::size_t extra_space(const string_t& s) noexcept
7801  {
7802  return std::accumulate(s.begin(), s.end(), size_t{},
7803  [](size_t res, typename string_t::value_type c)
7804  {
7805  switch (c)
7806  {
7807  case '"':
7808  case '\\':
7809  case '\b':
7810  case '\f':
7811  case '\n':
7812  case '\r':
7813  case '\t':
7814  {
7815  // from c (1 byte) to \x (2 bytes)
7816  return res + 1;
7817  }
7818 
7819  default:
7820  {
7821  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f)
7822  {
7823  // from c (1 byte) to \uxxxx (6 bytes)
7824  return res + 5;
7825  }
7826 
7827  return res;
7828  }
7829  }
7830  });
7831  }
7832 
7833  /*!
7834  @brief escape a string
7835 
7836  Escape a string by replacing certain special characters by a sequence of
7837  an escape character (backslash) and another character and other control
7838  characters by a sequence of "\u" followed by a four-digit hex
7839  representation.
7840 
7841  @param[in] s the string to escape
7842  @return the escaped string
7843 
7844  @complexity Linear in the length of string @a s.
7845  */
7846  static string_t escape_string(const string_t& s)
7847  {
7848  const auto space = extra_space(s);
7849  if (space == 0)
7850  {
7851  return s;
7852  }
7853 
7854  // create a result string of necessary size
7855  string_t result(s.size() + space, '\\');
7856  std::size_t pos = 0;
7857 
7858  for (const auto& c : s)
7859  {
7860  switch (c)
7861  {
7862  // quotation mark (0x22)
7863  case '"':
7864  {
7865  result[pos + 1] = '"';
7866  pos += 2;
7867  break;
7868  }
7869 
7870  // reverse solidus (0x5c)
7871  case '\\':
7872  {
7873  // nothing to change
7874  pos += 2;
7875  break;
7876  }
7877 
7878  // backspace (0x08)
7879  case '\b':
7880  {
7881  result[pos + 1] = 'b';
7882  pos += 2;
7883  break;
7884  }
7885 
7886  // formfeed (0x0c)
7887  case '\f':
7888  {
7889  result[pos + 1] = 'f';
7890  pos += 2;
7891  break;
7892  }
7893 
7894  // newline (0x0a)
7895  case '\n':
7896  {
7897  result[pos + 1] = 'n';
7898  pos += 2;
7899  break;
7900  }
7901 
7902  // carriage return (0x0d)
7903  case '\r':
7904  {
7905  result[pos + 1] = 'r';
7906  pos += 2;
7907  break;
7908  }
7909 
7910  // horizontal tab (0x09)
7911  case '\t':
7912  {
7913  result[pos + 1] = 't';
7914  pos += 2;
7915  break;
7916  }
7917 
7918  default:
7919  {
7920  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f)
7921  {
7922  // convert a number 0..15 to its hex representation
7923  // (0..f)
7924  static const char hexify[16] =
7925  {
7926  '0', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7',
7927  '8', '9', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f'
7928  };
7929 
7930  // print character c as \uxxxx
7931  for (const char m :
7932  { 'u', '0', '0', hexify[c >> 4], hexify[c & 0x0f]
7933  })
7934  {
7935  result[++pos] = m;
7936  }
7937 
7938  ++pos;
7939  }
7940  else
7941  {
7942  // all other characters are added as-is
7943  result[pos++] = c;
7944  }
7945  break;
7946  }
7947  }
7948  }
7949 
7950  return result;
7951  }
7952 
7953  /*!
7954  @brief internal implementation of the serialization function
7955 
7956  This function is called by the public member function dump and organizes
7957  the serialization internally. The indentation level is propagated as
7958  additional parameter. In case of arrays and objects, the function is
7959  called recursively. Note that
7960 
7961  - strings and object keys are escaped using `escape_string()`
7962  - integer numbers are converted implicitly via `operator<<`
7963  - floating-point numbers are converted to a string using `"%g"` format
7964 
7965  @param[out] o stream to write to
7966  @param[in] pretty_print whether the output shall be pretty-printed
7967  @param[in] indent_step the indent level
7968  @param[in] current_indent the current indent level (only used internally)
7969  */
7970  void dump(std::ostream& o,
7971  const bool pretty_print,
7972  const unsigned int indent_step,
7973  const unsigned int current_indent = 0) const
7974  {
7975  // variable to hold indentation for recursive calls
7976  unsigned int new_indent = current_indent;
7977 
7978  switch (m_type)
7979  {
7980  case value_t::object:
7981  {
7982  if (m_value.object->empty())
7983  {
7984  o << "{}";
7985  return;
7986  }
7987 
7988  o << "{";
7989 
7990  // increase indentation
7991  if (pretty_print)
7992  {
7993  new_indent += indent_step;
7994  o << "\n";
7995  }
7996 
7997  for (auto i = m_value.object->cbegin(); i != m_value.object->cend(); ++i)
7998  {
7999  if (i != m_value.object->cbegin())
8000  {
8001  o << (pretty_print ? ",\n" : ",");
8002  }
8003  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') << "\""
8004  << escape_string(i->first) << "\":"
8005  << (pretty_print ? " " : "");
8006  i->second.dump(o, pretty_print, indent_step, new_indent);
8007  }
8008 
8009  // decrease indentation
8010  if (pretty_print)
8011  {
8012  new_indent -= indent_step;
8013  o << "\n";
8014  }
8015 
8016  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') + "}";
8017  return;
8018  }
8019 
8020  case value_t::array:
8021  {
8022  if (m_value.array->empty())
8023  {
8024  o << "[]";
8025  return;
8026  }
8027 
8028  o << "[";
8029 
8030  // increase indentation
8031  if (pretty_print)
8032  {
8033  new_indent += indent_step;
8034  o << "\n";
8035  }
8036 
8037  for (auto i = m_value.array->cbegin(); i != m_value.array->cend(); ++i)
8038  {
8039  if (i != m_value.array->cbegin())
8040  {
8041  o << (pretty_print ? ",\n" : ",");
8042  }
8043  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ');
8044  i->dump(o, pretty_print, indent_step, new_indent);
8045  }
8046 
8047  // decrease indentation
8048  if (pretty_print)
8049  {
8050  new_indent -= indent_step;
8051  o << "\n";
8052  }
8053 
8054  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') << "]";
8055  return;
8056  }
8057 
8058  case value_t::string:
8059  {
8060  o << string_t("\"") << escape_string(*m_value.string) << "\"";
8061  return;
8062  }
8063 
8064  case value_t::boolean:
8065  {
8066  o << (m_value.boolean ? "true" : "false");
8067  return;
8068  }
8069 
8070  case value_t::number_integer:
8071  {
8072  o << m_value.number_integer;
8073  return;
8074  }
8075 
8076  case value_t::number_unsigned:
8077  {
8078  o << m_value.number_unsigned;
8079  return;
8080  }
8081 
8082  case value_t::number_float:
8083  {
8084  if (m_value.number_float == 0)
8085  {
8086  // special case for zero to get "0.0"/"-0.0"
8087  o << (std::signbit(m_value.number_float) ? "-0.0" : "0.0");
8088  }
8089  else
8090  {
8091  o << m_value.number_float;
8092  }
8093  return;
8094  }
8095 
8096  case value_t::discarded:
8097  {
8098  o << "<discarded>";
8099  return;
8100  }
8101 
8102  case value_t::null:
8103  {
8104  o << "null";
8105  return;
8106  }
8107  }
8108  }
8109 
8110  private:
8111  //////////////////////
8112  // member variables //
8113  //////////////////////
8114 
8115  /// the type of the current element
8116  value_t m_type = value_t::null;
8117 
8118  /// the value of the current element
8119  json_value m_value = {};
8120 
8121 
8122  private:
8123  ///////////////
8124  // iterators //
8125  ///////////////
8126 
8127  /*!
8128  @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
8129 
8130  This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
8131  string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
8132  to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
8133  a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
8134  end_value (`1`) models past the end.
8135  */
8136  class primitive_iterator_t
8137  {
8138  public:
8139  /// set iterator to a defined beginning
8140  void set_begin() noexcept
8141  {
8142  m_it = begin_value;
8143  }
8144 
8145  /// set iterator to a defined past the end
8146  void set_end() noexcept
8147  {
8148  m_it = end_value;
8149  }
8150 
8151  /// return whether the iterator can be dereferenced
8152  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
8153  {
8154  return (m_it == begin_value);
8155  }
8156 
8157  /// return whether the iterator is at end
8158  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
8159  {
8160  return (m_it == end_value);
8161  }
8162 
8163  /// return reference to the value to change and compare
8164  operator difference_type& () noexcept
8165  {
8166  return m_it;
8167  }
8168 
8169  /// return value to compare
8170  constexpr operator difference_type () const noexcept
8171  {
8172  return m_it;
8173  }
8174 
8175  private:
8176  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
8177  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
8178 
8179  /// iterator as signed integer type
8180  difference_type m_it = std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::denorm_min();
8181  };
8182 
8183  /*!
8184  @brief an iterator value
8185 
8186  @note This structure could easily be a union, but MSVC currently does not
8187  allow unions members with complex constructors, see
8188  https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/105.
8189  */
8190  struct internal_iterator
8191  {
8192  /// iterator for JSON objects
8193  typename object_t::iterator object_iterator;
8194  /// iterator for JSON arrays
8195  typename array_t::iterator array_iterator;
8196  /// generic iterator for all other types
8197  primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator;
8198 
8199  /// create an uninitialized internal_iterator
8200  internal_iterator() noexcept
8201  : object_iterator(), array_iterator(), primitive_iterator()
8202  {}
8203  };
8204 
8205  /// proxy class for the iterator_wrapper functions
8206  template<typename IteratorType>
8207  class iteration_proxy
8208  {
8209  private:
8210  /// helper class for iteration
8211  class iteration_proxy_internal
8212  {
8213  private:
8214  /// the iterator
8215  IteratorType anchor;
8216  /// an index for arrays (used to create key names)
8217  size_t array_index = 0;
8218 
8219  public:
8220  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept
8221  : anchor(it)
8222  {}
8223 
8224  /// dereference operator (needed for range-based for)
8225  iteration_proxy_internal& operator*()
8226  {
8227  return *this;
8228  }
8229 
8230  /// increment operator (needed for range-based for)
8231  iteration_proxy_internal& operator++()
8232  {
8233  ++anchor;
8234  ++array_index;
8235 
8236  return *this;
8237  }
8238 
8239  /// inequality operator (needed for range-based for)
8240  bool operator!= (const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const
8241  {
8242  return anchor != o.anchor;
8243  }
8244 
8245  /// return key of the iterator
8246  typename basic_json::string_t key() const
8247  {
8248  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
8249 
8250  switch (anchor.m_object->type())
8251  {
8252  // use integer array index as key
8253  case value_t::array:
8254  {
8255  return std::to_string(array_index);
8256  }
8257 
8258  // use key from the object
8259  case value_t::object:
8260  {
8261  return anchor.key();
8262  }
8263 
8264  // use an empty key for all primitive types
8265  default:
8266  {
8267  return "";
8268  }
8269  }
8270  }
8271 
8272  /// return value of the iterator
8273  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
8274  {
8275  return anchor.value();
8276  }
8277  };
8278 
8279  /// the container to iterate
8280  typename IteratorType::reference container;
8281 
8282  public:
8283  /// construct iteration proxy from a container
8284  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont)
8285  : container(cont)
8286  {}
8287 
8288  /// return iterator begin (needed for range-based for)
8289  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept
8290  {
8291  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
8292  }
8293 
8294  /// return iterator end (needed for range-based for)
8295  iteration_proxy_internal end() noexcept
8296  {
8297  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.end());
8298  }
8299  };
8300 
8301  public:
8302  /*!
8303  @brief a template for a random access iterator for the @ref basic_json class
8304 
8305  This class implements a both iterators (iterator and const_iterator) for the
8306  @ref basic_json class.
8307 
8308  @note An iterator is called *initialized* when a pointer to a JSON value
8309  has been set (e.g., by a constructor or a copy assignment). If the
8310  iterator is default-constructed, it is *uninitialized* and most
8311  methods are undefined. **The library uses assertions to detect calls
8312  on uninitialized iterators.**
8313 
8314  @requirement The class satisfies the following concept requirements:
8315  - [RandomAccessIterator](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/RandomAccessIterator):
8316  The iterator that can be moved to point (forward and backward) to any
8317  element in constant time.
8318 
8319  @since version 1.0.0, simplified in version 2.0.9
8320  */
8321  template<typename U>
8322  class iter_impl : public std::iterator<std::random_access_iterator_tag, U>
8323  {
8324  /// allow basic_json to access private members
8325  friend class basic_json;
8326 
8327  // make sure U is basic_json or const basic_json
8328  static_assert(std::is_same<U, basic_json>::value
8329  or std::is_same<U, const basic_json>::value,
8330  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
8331 
8332  public:
8333  /// the type of the values when the iterator is dereferenced
8334  using value_type = typename basic_json::value_type;
8335  /// a type to represent differences between iterators
8336  using difference_type = typename basic_json::difference_type;
8337  /// defines a pointer to the type iterated over (value_type)
8338  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<U>::value,
8339  typename basic_json::const_pointer,
8340  typename basic_json::pointer>::type;
8341  /// defines a reference to the type iterated over (value_type)
8342  using reference = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<U>::value,
8343  typename basic_json::const_reference,
8344  typename basic_json::reference>::type;
8345  /// the category of the iterator
8346  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
8347 
8348  /// default constructor
8349  iter_impl() = default;
8350 
8351  /*!
8352  @brief constructor for a given JSON instance
8353  @param[in] object pointer to a JSON object for this iterator
8354  @pre object != nullptr
8355  @post The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8356  */
8357  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept
8358  : m_object(object)
8359  {
8360  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8361 
8362  switch (m_object->m_type)
8363  {
8364  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8365  {
8366  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
8367  break;
8368  }
8369 
8370  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8371  {
8372  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
8373  break;
8374  }
8375 
8376  default:
8377  {
8378  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
8379  break;
8380  }
8381  }
8382  }
8383 
8384  /*
8385  Use operator `const_iterator` instead of `const_iterator(const iterator&
8386  other) noexcept` to avoid two class definitions for @ref iterator and
8387  @ref const_iterator.
8388 
8389  This function is only called if this class is an @ref iterator. If this
8390  class is a @ref const_iterator this function is not called.
8391  */
8392  operator const_iterator() const
8393  {
8394  const_iterator ret;
8395 
8396  if (m_object)
8397  {
8398  ret.m_object = m_object;
8399  ret.m_it = m_it;
8400  }
8401 
8402  return ret;
8403  }
8404 
8405  /*!
8406  @brief copy constructor
8407  @param[in] other iterator to copy from
8408  @note It is not checked whether @a other is initialized.
8409  */
8410  iter_impl(const iter_impl& other) noexcept
8411  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
8412  {}
8413 
8414  /*!
8415  @brief copy assignment
8416  @param[in,out] other iterator to copy from
8417  @note It is not checked whether @a other is initialized.
8418  */
8419  iter_impl& operator=(iter_impl other) noexcept(
8420  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<pointer>::value and
8421  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<pointer>::value and
8422  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<internal_iterator>::value and
8423  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<internal_iterator>::value
8424  )
8425  {
8426  std::swap(m_object, other.m_object);
8427  std::swap(m_it, other.m_it);
8428  return *this;
8429  }
8430 
8431  private:
8432  /*!
8433  @brief set the iterator to the first value
8434  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8435  */
8436  void set_begin() noexcept
8437  {
8438  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8439 
8440  switch (m_object->m_type)
8441  {
8442  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8443  {
8444  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
8445  break;
8446  }
8447 
8448  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8449  {
8450  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
8451  break;
8452  }
8453 
8454  case basic_json::value_t::null:
8455  {
8456  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
8457  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8458  break;
8459  }
8460 
8461  default:
8462  {
8463  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
8464  break;
8465  }
8466  }
8467  }
8468 
8469  /*!
8470  @brief set the iterator past the last value
8471  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8472  */
8473  void set_end() noexcept
8474  {
8475  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8476 
8477  switch (m_object->m_type)
8478  {
8479  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8480  {
8481  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
8482  break;
8483  }
8484 
8485  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8486  {
8487  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
8488  break;
8489  }
8490 
8491  default:
8492  {
8493  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8494  break;
8495  }
8496  }
8497  }
8498 
8499  public:
8500  /*!
8501  @brief return a reference to the value pointed to by the iterator
8502  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8503  */
8504  reference operator*() const
8505  {
8506  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8507 
8508  switch (m_object->m_type)
8509  {
8510  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8511  {
8512  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
8513  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
8514  }
8515 
8516  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8517  {
8518  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
8519  return *m_it.array_iterator;
8520  }
8521 
8522  case basic_json::value_t::null:
8523  {
8524  throw std::out_of_range("cannot get value");
8525  }
8526 
8527  default:
8528  {
8529  if (m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())
8530  {
8531  return *m_object;
8532  }
8533 
8534  throw std::out_of_range("cannot get value");
8535  }
8536  }
8537  }
8538 
8539  /*!
8540  @brief dereference the iterator
8541  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8542  */
8543  pointer operator->() const
8544  {
8545  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8546 
8547  switch (m_object->m_type)
8548  {
8549  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8550  {
8551  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
8552  return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
8553  }
8554 
8555  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8556  {
8557  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
8558  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
8559  }
8560 
8561  default:
8562  {
8563  if (m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())
8564  {
8565  return m_object;
8566  }
8567 
8568  throw std::out_of_range("cannot get value");
8569  }
8570  }
8571  }
8572 
8573  /*!
8574  @brief post-increment (it++)
8575  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8576  */
8577  iter_impl operator++(int)
8578  {
8579  auto result = *this;
8580  ++(*this);
8581  return result;
8582  }
8583 
8584  /*!
8585  @brief pre-increment (++it)
8586  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8587  */
8588  iter_impl& operator++()
8589  {
8590  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8591 
8592  switch (m_object->m_type)
8593  {
8594  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8595  {
8596  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
8597  break;
8598  }
8599 
8600  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8601  {
8602  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
8603  break;
8604  }
8605 
8606  default:
8607  {
8608  ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
8609  break;
8610  }
8611  }
8612 
8613  return *this;
8614  }
8615 
8616  /*!
8617  @brief post-decrement (it--)
8618  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8619  */
8620  iter_impl operator--(int)
8621  {
8622  auto result = *this;
8623  --(*this);
8624  return result;
8625  }
8626 
8627  /*!
8628  @brief pre-decrement (--it)
8629  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8630  */
8631  iter_impl& operator--()
8632  {
8633  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8634 
8635  switch (m_object->m_type)
8636  {
8637  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8638  {
8639  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
8640  break;
8641  }
8642 
8643  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8644  {
8645  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
8646  break;
8647  }
8648 
8649  default:
8650  {
8651  --m_it.primitive_iterator;
8652  break;
8653  }
8654  }
8655 
8656  return *this;
8657  }
8658 
8659  /*!
8660  @brief comparison: equal
8661  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8662  */
8663  bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
8664  {
8665  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8666  if (m_object != other.m_object)
8667  {
8668  throw std::domain_error("cannot compare iterators of different containers");
8669  }
8670 
8671  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8672 
8673  switch (m_object->m_type)
8674  {
8675  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8676  {
8677  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
8678  }
8679 
8680  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8681  {
8682  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
8683  }
8684 
8685  default:
8686  {
8687  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8688  }
8689  }
8690  }
8691 
8692  /*!
8693  @brief comparison: not equal
8694  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8695  */
8696  bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
8697  {
8698  return not operator==(other);
8699  }
8700 
8701  /*!
8702  @brief comparison: smaller
8703  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8704  */
8705  bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
8706  {
8707  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8708  if (m_object != other.m_object)
8709  {
8710  throw std::domain_error("cannot compare iterators of different containers");
8711  }
8712 
8713  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8714 
8715  switch (m_object->m_type)
8716  {
8717  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8718  {
8719  throw std::domain_error("cannot compare order of object iterators");
8720  }
8721 
8722  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8723  {
8724  return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
8725  }
8726 
8727  default:
8728  {
8729  return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8730  }
8731  }
8732  }
8733 
8734  /*!
8735  @brief comparison: less than or equal
8736  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8737  */
8738  bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const
8739  {
8740  return not other.operator < (*this);
8741  }
8742 
8743  /*!
8744  @brief comparison: greater than
8745  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8746  */
8747  bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const
8748  {
8749  return not operator<=(other);
8750  }
8751 
8752  /*!
8753  @brief comparison: greater than or equal
8754  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8755  */
8756  bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const
8757  {
8758  return not operator<(other);
8759  }
8760 
8761  /*!
8762  @brief add to iterator
8763  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8764  */
8765  iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
8766  {
8767  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8768 
8769  switch (m_object->m_type)
8770  {
8771  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8772  {
8773  throw std::domain_error("cannot use offsets with object iterators");
8774  }
8775 
8776  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8777  {
8778  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
8779  break;
8780  }
8781 
8782  default:
8783  {
8784  m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
8785  break;
8786  }
8787  }
8788
