8790  }
8791 
8792  /*!
8793  @brief subtract from iterator
8794  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8795  */
8796  iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i)
8797  {
8798  return operator+=(-i);
8799  }
8800 
8801  /*!
8802  @brief add to iterator
8803  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8804  */
8805  iter_impl operator+(difference_type i)
8806  {
8807  auto result = *this;
8808  result += i;
8809  return result;
8810  }
8811 
8812  /*!
8813  @brief subtract from iterator
8814  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8815  */
8816  iter_impl operator-(difference_type i)
8817  {
8818  auto result = *this;
8819  result -= i;
8820  return result;
8821  }
8822 
8823  /*!
8824  @brief return difference
8825  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8826  */
8827  difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
8828  {
8829  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8830 
8831  switch (m_object->m_type)
8832  {
8833  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8834  {
8835  throw std::domain_error("cannot use offsets with object iterators");
8836  }
8837 
8838  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8839  {
8840  return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
8841  }
8842 
8843  default:
8844  {
8845  return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
8846  }
8847  }
8848  }
8849 
8850  /*!
8851  @brief access to successor
8852  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8853  */
8854  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8855  {
8856  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8857 
8858  switch (m_object->m_type)
8859  {
8860  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8861  {
8862  throw std::domain_error("cannot use operator[] for object iterators");
8863  }
8864 
8865  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8866  {
8867  return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
8868  }
8869 
8870  case basic_json::value_t::null:
8871  {
8872  throw std::out_of_range("cannot get value");
8873  }
8874 
8875  default:
8876  {
8877  if (m_it.primitive_iterator == -n)
8878  {
8879  return *m_object;
8880  }
8881 
8882  throw std::out_of_range("cannot get value");
8883  }
8884  }
8885  }
8886 
8887  /*!
8888  @brief return the key of an object iterator
8889  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8890  */
8891  typename object_t::key_type key() const
8892  {
8893  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8894 
8895  if (m_object->is_object())
8896  {
8897  return m_it.object_iterator->first;
8898  }
8899 
8900  throw std::domain_error("cannot use key() for non-object iterators");
8901  }
8902 
8903  /*!
8904  @brief return the value of an iterator
8905  @pre The iterator is initialized; i.e. `m_object != nullptr`.
8906  */
8907  reference value() const
8908  {
8909  return operator*();
8910  }
8911 
8912  private:
8913  /// associated JSON instance
8914  pointer m_object = nullptr;
8915  /// the actual iterator of the associated instance
8916  internal_iterator m_it = internal_iterator();
8917  };
8918 
8919  /*!
8920  @brief a template for a reverse iterator class
8921 
8922  @tparam Base the base iterator type to reverse. Valid types are @ref
8923  iterator (to create @ref reverse_iterator) and @ref const_iterator (to
8924  create @ref const_reverse_iterator).
8925 
8926  @requirement The class satisfies the following concept requirements:
8927  - [RandomAccessIterator](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/RandomAccessIterator):
8928  The iterator that can be moved to point (forward and backward) to any
8929  element in constant time.
8930  - [OutputIterator](http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/concept/OutputIterator):
8931  It is possible to write to the pointed-to element (only if @a Base is
8932  @ref iterator).
8933 
8934  @since version 1.0.0
8935  */
8936  template<typename Base>
8937  class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
8938  {
8939  public:
8940  /// shortcut to the reverse iterator adaptor
8941  using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
8942  /// the reference type for the pointed-to element
8943  using reference = typename Base::reference;
8944 
8945  /// create reverse iterator from iterator
8946  json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept
8947  : base_iterator(it)
8948  {}
8949 
8950  /// create reverse iterator from base class
8951  json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept
8952  : base_iterator(it)
8953  {}
8954 
8955  /// post-increment (it++)
8956  json_reverse_iterator operator++(int)
8957  {
8958  return base_iterator::operator++(1);
8959  }
8960 
8961  /// pre-increment (++it)
8962  json_reverse_iterator& operator++()
8963  {
8964  base_iterator::operator++();
8965  return *this;
8966  }
8967 
8968  /// post-decrement (it--)
8969  json_reverse_iterator operator--(int)
8970  {
8971  return base_iterator::operator--(1);
8972  }
8973 
8974  /// pre-decrement (--it)
8975  json_reverse_iterator& operator--()
8976  {
8977  base_iterator::operator--();
8978  return *this;
8979  }
8980 
8981  /// add to iterator
8982  json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i)
8983  {
8984  base_iterator::operator+=(i);
8985  return *this;
8986  }
8987 
8988  /// add to iterator
8989  json_reverse_iterator operator+(difference_type i) const
8990  {
8991  auto result = *this;
8992  result += i;
8993  return result;
8994  }
8995 
8996  /// subtract from iterator
8997  json_reverse_iterator operator-(difference_type i) const
8998  {
8999  auto result = *this;
9000  result -= i;
9001  return result;
9002  }
9003 
9004  /// return difference
9005  difference_type operator-(const json_reverse_iterator& other) const
9006  {
9007  return this->base() - other.base();
9008  }
9009 
9010  /// access to successor
9011  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
9012  {
9013  return *(this->operator+(n));
9014  }
9015 
9016  /// return the key of an object iterator
9017  typename object_t::key_type key() const
9018  {
9019  auto it = --this->base();
9020  return it.key();
9021  }
9022 
9023  /// return the value of an iterator
9024  reference value() const
9025  {
9026  auto it = --this->base();
9027  return it.operator * ();
9028  }
9029  };
9030 
9031 
9032  private:
9033  //////////////////////
9034  // lexer and parser //
9035  //////////////////////
9036 
9037  /*!
9038  @brief lexical analysis
9039 
9040  This class organizes the lexical analysis during JSON deserialization. The
9041  core of it is a scanner generated by [re2c](http://re2c.org) that
9042  processes a buffer and recognizes tokens according to RFC 7159.
9043  */
9044  class lexer
9045  {
9046  public:
9047  /// token types for the parser
9048  enum class token_type
9049  {
9050  uninitialized, ///< indicating the scanner is uninitialized
9051  literal_true, ///< the `true` literal
9052  literal_false, ///< the `false` literal
9053  literal_null, ///< the `null` literal
9054  value_string, ///< a string -- use get_string() for actual value
9055  value_number, ///< a number -- use get_number() for actual value
9056  begin_array, ///< the character for array begin `[`
9057  begin_object, ///< the character for object begin `{`
9058  end_array, ///< the character for array end `]`
9059  end_object, ///< the character for object end `}`
9060  name_separator, ///< the name separator `:`
9061  value_separator, ///< the value separator `,`
9062  parse_error, ///< indicating a parse error
9063  end_of_input ///< indicating the end of the input buffer
9064  };
9065 
9066  /// the char type to use in the lexer
9067  using lexer_char_t = unsigned char;
9068 
9069  /// a lexer from a buffer with given length
9070  lexer(const lexer_char_t* buff, const size_t len) noexcept
9071  : m_content(buff)
9072  {
9073  assert(m_content != nullptr);
9074  m_start = m_cursor = m_content;
9075  m_limit = m_content + len;
9076  }
9077 
9078  /// a lexer from an input stream
9079  explicit lexer(std::istream& s)
9080  : m_stream(&s), m_line_buffer()
9081  {
9082  // immediately abort if stream is erroneous
9083  if (s.fail())
9084  {
9085  throw std::invalid_argument("stream error");
9086  }
9087 
9088  // fill buffer
9089  fill_line_buffer();
9090 
9091  // skip UTF-8 byte-order mark
9092  if (m_line_buffer.size() >= 3 and m_line_buffer.substr(0, 3) == "\xEF\xBB\xBF")
9093  {
9094  m_line_buffer[0] = ' ';
9095  m_line_buffer[1] = ' ';
9096  m_line_buffer[2] = ' ';
9097  }
9098  }
9099 
9100  // switch off unwanted functions (due to pointer members)
9101  lexer() = delete;
9102  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
9103  lexer operator=(const lexer&) = delete;
9104 
9105  /*!
9106  @brief create a string from one or two Unicode code points
9107 
9108  There are two cases: (1) @a codepoint1 is in the Basic Multilingual
9109  Plane (U+0000 through U+FFFF) and @a codepoint2 is 0, or (2)
9110  @a codepoint1 and @a codepoint2 are a UTF-16 surrogate pair to
9111  represent a code point above U+FFFF.
9112 
9113  @param[in] codepoint1 the code point (can be high surrogate)
9114  @param[in] codepoint2 the code point (can be low surrogate or 0)
9115 
9116  @return string representation of the code point; the length of the
9117  result string is between 1 and 4 characters.
9118 
9119  @throw std::out_of_range if code point is > 0x10ffff; example: `"code
9120  points above 0x10FFFF are invalid"`
9121  @throw std::invalid_argument if the low surrogate is invalid; example:
9122  `""missing or wrong low surrogate""`
9123 
9124  @complexity Constant.
9125 
9126  @see <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8#Sample_code>
9127  */
9128  static string_t to_unicode(const std::size_t codepoint1,
9129  const std::size_t codepoint2 = 0)
9130  {
9131  // calculate the code point from the given code points
9132  std::size_t codepoint = codepoint1;
9133 
9134  // check if codepoint1 is a high surrogate
9135  if (codepoint1 >= 0xD800 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
9136  {
9137  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
9138  if (codepoint2 >= 0xDC00 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF)
9139  {
9140  codepoint =
9141  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
9142  (codepoint1 << 10)
9143  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
9144  + codepoint2
9145  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
9146  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
9147  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
9148  - 0x35FDC00;
9149  }
9150  else
9151  {
9152  throw std::invalid_argument("missing or wrong low surrogate");
9153  }
9154  }
9155 
9156  string_t result;
9157 
9158  if (codepoint < 0x80)
9159  {
9160  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
9161  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(codepoint));
9162  }
9163  else if (codepoint <= 0x7ff)
9164  {
9165  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
9166  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xC0 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x1F)));
9167  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9168  }
9169  else if (codepoint <= 0xffff)
9170  {
9171  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
9172  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xE0 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x0F)));
9173  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
9174  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9175  }
9176  else if (codepoint <= 0x10ffff)
9177  {
9178  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
9179  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xF0 | ((codepoint >> 18) & 0x07)));
9180  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F)));
9181  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
9182  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9183  }
9184  else
9185  {
9186  throw std::out_of_range("code points above 0x10FFFF are invalid");
9187  }
9188 
9189  return result;
9190  }
9191 
9192  /// return name of values of type token_type (only used for errors)
9193  static std::string token_type_name(const token_type t)
9194  {
9195  switch (t)
9196  {
9197  case token_type::uninitialized:
9198  return "<uninitialized>";
9199  case token_type::literal_true:
9200  return "true literal";
9201  case token_type::literal_false:
9202  return "false literal";
9203  case token_type::literal_null:
9204  return "null literal";
9205  case token_type::value_string:
9206  return "string literal";
9207  case token_type::value_number:
9208  return "number literal";
9209  case token_type::begin_array:
9210  return "'['";
9211  case token_type::begin_object:
9212  return "'{'";
9213  case token_type::end_array:
9214  return "']'";
9215  case token_type::end_object:
9216  return "'}'";
9217  case token_type::name_separator:
9218  return "':'";
9219  case token_type::value_separator:
9220  return "','";
9221  case token_type::parse_error:
9222  return "<parse error>";
9223  case token_type::end_of_input:
9224  return "end of input";
9225  default:
9226  {
9227  // catch non-enum values
9228  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9229  }
9230  }
9231  }
9232 
9233  /*!
9234  This function implements a scanner for JSON. It is specified using
9235  regular expressions that try to follow RFC 7159 as close as possible.
9236  These regular expressions are then translated into a minimized
9237  deterministic finite automaton (DFA) by the tool
9238  [re2c](http://re2c.org). As a result, the translated code for this
9239  function consists of a large block of code with `goto` jumps.
9240 
9241  @return the class of the next token read from the buffer
9242 
9243  @complexity Linear in the length of the input.\n
9244 
9245  Proposition: The loop below will always terminate for finite input.\n
9246 
9247  Proof (by contradiction): Assume a finite input. To loop forever, the
9248  loop must never hit code with a `break` statement. The only code
9249  snippets without a `break` statement are the continue statements for
9250  whitespace and byte-order-marks. To loop forever, the input must be an
9251  infinite sequence of whitespace or byte-order-marks. This contradicts
9252  the assumption of finite input, q.e.d.
9253  */
9254  token_type scan()
9255  {
9256  while (true)
9257  {
9258  // pointer for backtracking information
9259  m_marker = nullptr;
9260 
9261  // remember the begin of the token
9262  m_start = m_cursor;
9263  assert(m_start != nullptr);
9264 
9265 
9266  {
9267  lexer_char_t yych;
9268  unsigned int yyaccept = 0;
9269  static const unsigned char yybm[] =
9270  {
9271  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9272  0, 32, 32, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0,
9273  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9274  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9275  160, 128, 0, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9276  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9277  192, 192, 192, 192, 192, 192, 192, 192,
9278  192, 192, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9279  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9280  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9281  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9282  128, 128, 128, 128, 0, 128, 128, 128,
9283  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9284  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9285  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9286  128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128, 128,
9287  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9288  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9289  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9290  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9291  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9292  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9293  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9294  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9295  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9296  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9297  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9298  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9299  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9300  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9301  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9302  0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
9303  };
9304  if ((m_limit - m_cursor) < 5)
9305  {
9306  fill_line_buffer(5); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9307  }
9308  yych = *m_cursor;
9309  if (yybm[0 + yych] & 32)
9310  {
9311  goto basic_json_parser_6;
9312  }
9313  if (yych <= '[')
9314  {
9315  if (yych <= '-')
9316  {
9317  if (yych <= '"')
9318  {
9319  if (yych <= 0x00)
9320  {
9321  goto basic_json_parser_2;
9322  }
9323  if (yych <= '!')
9324  {
9325  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9326  }
9327  goto basic_json_parser_9;
9328  }
9329  else
9330  {
9331  if (yych <= '+')
9332  {
9333  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9334  }
9335  if (yych <= ',')
9336  {
9337  goto basic_json_parser_10;
9338  }
9339  goto basic_json_parser_12;
9340  }
9341  }
9342  else
9343  {
9344  if (yych <= '9')
9345  {
9346  if (yych <= '/')
9347  {
9348  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9349  }
9350  if (yych <= '0')
9351  {
9352  goto basic_json_parser_13;
9353  }
9354  goto basic_json_parser_15;
9355  }
9356  else
9357  {
9358  if (yych <= ':')
9359  {
9360  goto basic_json_parser_17;
9361  }
9362  if (yych <= 'Z')
9363  {
9364  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9365  }
9366  goto basic_json_parser_19;
9367  }
9368  }
9369  }
9370  else
9371  {
9372  if (yych <= 'n')
9373  {
9374  if (yych <= 'e')
9375  {
9376  if (yych == ']')
9377  {
9378  goto basic_json_parser_21;
9379  }
9380  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9381  }
9382  else
9383  {
9384  if (yych <= 'f')
9385  {
9386  goto basic_json_parser_23;
9387  }
9388  if (yych <= 'm')
9389  {
9390  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9391  }
9392  goto basic_json_parser_24;
9393  }
9394  }
9395  else
9396  {
9397  if (yych <= 'z')
9398  {
9399  if (yych == 't')
9400  {
9401  goto basic_json_parser_25;
9402  }
9403  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9404  }
9405  else
9406  {
9407  if (yych <= '{')
9408  {
9409  goto basic_json_parser_26;
9410  }
9411  if (yych == '}')
9412  {
9413  goto basic_json_parser_28;
9414  }
9415  goto basic_json_parser_4;
9416  }
9417  }
9418  }
9419 basic_json_parser_2:
9420  ++m_cursor;
9421  {
9422  last_token_type = token_type::end_of_input;
9423  break;
9424  }
9425 basic_json_parser_4:
9426  ++m_cursor;
9427 basic_json_parser_5:
9428  {
9429  last_token_type = token_type::parse_error;
9430  break;
9431  }
9432 basic_json_parser_6:
9433  ++m_cursor;
9434  if (m_limit <= m_cursor)
9435  {
9436  fill_line_buffer(1); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9437  }
9438  yych = *m_cursor;
9439  if (yybm[0 + yych] & 32)
9440  {
9441  goto basic_json_parser_6;
9442  }
9443  {
9444  continue;
9445  }
9446 basic_json_parser_9:
9447  yyaccept = 0;
9448  yych = *(m_marker = ++m_cursor);
9449  if (yych <= 0x1F)
9450  {
9451  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9452  }
9453  if (yych <= 0x7F)
9454  {
9455  goto basic_json_parser_31;
9456  }
9457  if (yych <= 0xC1)
9458  {
9459  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9460  }
9461  if (yych <= 0xF4)
9462  {
9463  goto basic_json_parser_31;
9464  }
9465  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9466 basic_json_parser_10:
9467  ++m_cursor;
9468  {
9469  last_token_type = token_type::value_separator;
9470  break;
9471  }
9472 basic_json_parser_12:
9473  yych = *++m_cursor;
9474  if (yych <= '/')
9475  {
9476  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9477  }
9478  if (yych <= '0')
9479  {
9480  goto basic_json_parser_13;
9481  }
9482  if (yych <= '9')
9483  {
9484  goto basic_json_parser_15;
9485  }
9486  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9487 basic_json_parser_13:
9488  yyaccept = 1;
9489  yych = *(m_marker = ++m_cursor);
9490  if (yych <= 'D')
9491  {
9492  if (yych == '.')
9493  {
9494  goto basic_json_parser_43;
9495  }
9496  }
9497  else
9498  {
9499  if (yych <= 'E')
9500  {
9501  goto basic_json_parser_44;
9502  }
9503  if (yych == 'e')
9504  {
9505  goto basic_json_parser_44;
9506  }
9507  }
9508 basic_json_parser_14:
9509  {
9510  last_token_type = token_type::value_number;
9511  break;
9512  }
9513 basic_json_parser_15:
9514  yyaccept = 1;
9515  m_marker = ++m_cursor;
9516  if ((m_limit - m_cursor) < 3)
9517  {
9518  fill_line_buffer(3); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9519  }
9520  yych = *m_cursor;
9521  if (yybm[0 + yych] & 64)
9522  {
9523  goto basic_json_parser_15;
9524  }
9525  if (yych <= 'D')
9526  {
9527  if (yych == '.')
9528  {
9529  goto basic_json_parser_43;
9530  }
9531  goto basic_json_parser_14;
9532  }
9533  else
9534  {
9535  if (yych <= 'E')
9536  {
9537  goto basic_json_parser_44;
9538  }
9539  if (yych == 'e')
9540  {
9541  goto basic_json_parser_44;
9542  }
9543  goto basic_json_parser_14;
9544  }
9545 basic_json_parser_17:
9546  ++m_cursor;
9547  {
9548  last_token_type = token_type::name_separator;
9549  break;
9550  }
9551 basic_json_parser_19:
9552  ++m_cursor;
9553  {
9554  last_token_type = token_type::begin_array;
9555  break;
9556  }
9557 basic_json_parser_21:
9558  ++m_cursor;
9559  {
9560  last_token_type = token_type::end_array;
9561  break;
9562  }
9563 basic_json_parser_23:
9564  yyaccept = 0;
9565  yych = *(m_marker = ++m_cursor);
9566  if (yych == 'a')
9567  {
9568  goto basic_json_parser_45;
9569  }
9570  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9571 basic_json_parser_24:
9572  yyaccept = 0;
9573  yych = *(m_marker = ++m_cursor);
9574  if (yych == 'u')
9575  {
9576  goto basic_json_parser_46;
9577  }
9578  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9579 basic_json_parser_25:
9580  yyaccept = 0;
9581  yych = *(m_marker = ++m_cursor);
9582  if (yych == 'r')
9583  {
9584  goto basic_json_parser_47;
9585  }
9586  goto basic_json_parser_5;
9587 basic_json_parser_26:
9588  ++m_cursor;
9589  {
9590  last_token_type = token_type::begin_object;
9591  break;
9592  }
9593 basic_json_parser_28:
9594  ++m_cursor;
9595  {
9596  last_token_type = token_type::end_object;
9597  break;
9598  }
9599 basic_json_parser_30:
9600  ++m_cursor;
9601  if (m_limit <= m_cursor)
9602  {
9603  fill_line_buffer(1); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9604  }
9605  yych = *m_cursor;
9606 basic_json_parser_31:
9607  if (yybm[0 + yych] & 128)
9608  {
9609  goto basic_json_parser_30;
9610  }
9611  if (yych <= 0xE0)
9612  {
9613  if (yych <= '\\')
9614  {
9615  if (yych <= 0x1F)
9616  {
